.SH NAME
Bitcoin::Crypto::BIP44 \- BIP44 (multi\-account hierarchy) implementation
.SH SYNOPSIS
.IX Header "SYNOPSIS"
.Vb 1
\&        use Bitcoin::Crypto::BIP44;
\&
\&        my $path = Bitcoin::Crypto::BIP44\->new(
\&                coin_type => Bitcoin::Crypto::Network\->get(\*(Aqbitcoin_testnet\*(Aq), # can also be a number or a key instance
\&                index => 43,
\&                # account => 0,
\&                # change => 0,
\&        );
\&
\&        # stringifies automatically
\&        say "$path";
\&
\&        # can be used in key derivation
\&        $ext_private_key\->derive_key($path);
.Ve
.SH DESCRIPTION
.IX Header "DESCRIPTION"
This class is a helper for constructing BIP44\-compilant key derivation paths.
BIP44 describes the mechanism the HD (Hierarchical Deterministic) wallets use
to decide derivation paths for coins. BIP49 and BIP84 are constructed the same
way, but used for compat and segwit addresses respectively.
.PP
Each coin has its own \f(CW\*(C`coin_type\*(C'\fR constant, a list of which is maintained
here: <https://github.com/satoshilabs/slips/blob/master/slip\-0044.md>.
Bitcoin::Crypto::Network instances hold these constants under the
\&\f(CW\*(C`bip44_coin\*(C'\fR property.
.PP
BIP44 objects stringify automatically and can be directly used in
"derive_key" in Bitcoin::Crypto::Key::ExtPrivate method. In return, any key
object can be used as \f(CW\*(C`coin_type\*(C'\fR in "new", which will automatically fetch
coin_type number from the key\*(Aqs current network.
.SH INTERFACE
.IX Header "INTERFACE"
.SS Attributes
.IX Subsection "Attributes"
Refer to <https://github.com/bitcoin/bips/blob/master/bip\-0044.mediawiki> for
details of those attributes.
.PP
All of these attributes can be fetched using a method with the same name.
.PP
\fIpurpose\fR
.IX Subsection "purpose"
.PP
Purpose contains the BIP document number that you wish to use. Can be either
\&\f(CW44\fR, \f(CW49\fR, \f(CW84\fR or \f(CW86\fR.
.PP
By default, number \f(CW44\fR will be used.
.PP
\fIcoin_type\fR
.IX Subsection "coin_type"
.PP
Needs to be a non\-negative integer number. It should be less than \f(CW\*(C`2^31\*(C'\fR (but
will not check for that).
.PP
Will also accept key objects and network objects, as it is possible to fetch
the constant for them. In this case, it might raise an exception if the network
does not contain the \f(CW\*(C`bip44_coin\*(C'\fR constant.
.PP
This value should be in line with the table of BIP44 constants mentioned above.
.PP
By default, the value defined in the current default network will be used: see
Bitcoin::Crypto::Network.
.PP
\fIaccount\fR
.IX Subsection "account"
.PP
Needs to be a non\-negative integer number. It should be less than \f(CW\*(C`2^31\*(C'\fR (but
will not check for that).
.PP
By default, the value \f(CW0\fR is used.
.PP
\fIchange\fR
.IX Subsection "change"
.PP
Needs to be a number \f(CW1\fR (for addresses to be used as change outputs) or \f(CW0\fR
(for addresses that are to be used for receiving from external sources).
.PP
By default, the value \f(CW0\fR is used.
.PP
\fIindex\fR
.IX Subsection "index"
.PP
Needs to be a non\-negative integer number. It should be less than \f(CW\*(C`2^31\*(C'\fR (but
will not check for that).
.PP
By default, the value \f(CW0\fR is used.
.PP
\fIpublic\fR
.IX Subsection "public"
.PP
Use \f(CW\*(C`public\*(C'\fR if you want to derive a public extended key. This is a must when
deriving BIP44 from extended public keys.
.PP
Since it isn\*(Aqt possible to derive full BIP44 path with public derivation
scheme, this will assume "get_from_account".
.PP
\fIget_account\fR
.IX Subsection "get_account"
.PP
If passed \f(CW1\fR, the resulting derivation path will only go as far as to the
account part. "index" and "change" values will be ignored. Use this to get
extended key for the account.
.PP
By default, you will get the full derivation path.
.PP
\fIget_from_account\fR
.IX Subsection "get_from_account"
.PP
If passed \f(CW1\fR, the resulting derivation path will start after the account
part. "purpose", "coin_type" and "account" values will be ignored. Use
this to further derive key that was only derived up to the account part.
.PP
By default, you will get the full derivation path.
.SS Methods
.IX Subsection "Methods"
\fInew\fR
.IX Subsection "new"
.PP
.Vb 1
\&        $bip_object = $class\->new(%data)
.Ve
.PP
This is a standard Moo constructor, which can be used to create the object. It
takes arguments specified in "Attributes".
.PP
Returns class instance.
.PP
\fIas_string\fR
.IX Subsection "as_string"
.PP
.Vb 1
\&        $path = $object\->as_string()
.Ve
.PP
Stringifies the object as BIP44\-compilant key derivation path. Can be used
indirectly by just stringifying the object.
.PP
\fIget_derivation_path\fR
.IX Subsection "get_derivation_path"
.PP
.Vb 1
